## v4.0.0 (2026-05-09)

**Changed by:** ProjectOdyssey CI investigation of Mojo 1.0.0b2 KGEN +0x6ef7b/+0x6c156/+0x6fc27 crash
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

- **MAJOR bump (3.9.0 → 4.0.0):** New crash signature for Mojo 1.0.0b2 added; recommended
  investigation flow restructured around parallel-hypothesis sub-agent dispatch
- Added "Mojo 1.0.0b2 Crash 4 — KGEN +0x6ef7b/+0x6c156/+0x6fc27" section
- Added 4-hypothesis disproof checklist as starter for future non-deterministic JIT crashes:
  1. Tuple destructor UAF
  2. Memory pressure
  3. Import volume
  4. Sequential test-group leak
- Added Sanitizer Escalation matrix (ASAN; TSAN+MSAN+UBSAN) for when local hypotheses cannot
  reproduce the crash
- Added 7-step Investigation Playbook for any future non-deterministic JIT crash
- Added 2 Failed Attempts rows: sequential vs parallel hypothesis dispatch (~4x wall-clock
  cost saved by parallel); filing upstream without sanitizer evidence
- Description trigger list extended with conditions 17-19 (Mojo 1.0.0b2 crash, parallel
  hypothesis sub-agents, sanitizer agents)
- Date bumped to 2026-05-09; verification level: `verified-local` (sanitizer agents still
  running at amendment time — local 4-hypothesis disproof complete)

### Why

The previous skill (v3.9.0) covered Mojo 0.26.x crash types deterministically. Mojo 1.0.0b2
introduced a new non-deterministic crash that defeats local repro entirely. The
parallel-hypothesis-sub-agent methodology proved itself in ProjectOdyssey: 4 agents
disproved 4 hypotheses simultaneously (0/161+ local repros each), establishing in one
parallel wave what would have taken hours sequentially. Documenting this as a starting
checklist accelerates future investigations.

### Outstanding (carry into v4.0.1+ amendments)

- Sanitizer agent results (ASAN; TSAN+MSAN+UBSAN) — running at amendment time, results
  pending
- Once sanitizers report, this skill should be amended to `verified-ci` if the upstream
  fix lands, or with the workaround if root cause is identified

